## 8) Operational Runbook (Daily High-Level Checklist)

1. Fetch operational data up to cutoff.
2. Validate schema/completeness and stop on critical missing data.
3. Build time-safe features.
4. Generate distributional forecast.
5. Apply post-hoc calibration.
6. Convert to contract bucket probabilities.
7. Pull market prices and compute EV net costs.
8. Place orders only if edge and risk constraints pass.
9. Persist logs/artifacts for audit and post-mortem.

---

## 9) Definition of Done for “Production Ready”

A city is production ready only when all are true:
- Contract-aligned target and bucketization validated.
- Holdout reliability/calibration acceptable in relevant regimes.
- Contract-level Brier beats required baselines.
- Backtested EV positive after conservative costs.
- Drawdown/exposure/kill-switch constraints validated.
- Daily runbook executes deterministically with complete audit artifacts.

